Item 3.5 — Evidence creation loop with idempotency
This is the core of Flow 3D. For each Applicability row, we check whether an Evidence record already exists. If not, we create one. Idempotency matters because the flow fires on every Stage 3 gate tick — we don't want duplicates on re-ticks.
Add these actions below List Active Applicability For Cycle, still inside the False branch of Prior Gates Incomplete.
Action 1 — Apply to each: Loop Active Applicability

Connector: Control → Apply to each
Select an output from previous steps: click into the field → dynamic content panel → select value from List Active Applicability For Cycle
Rename the action to: Loop Active Applicability

Everything below goes inside this loop.
Action 2 — List rows: Find Existing Evidence
Purpose: check whether an Evidence record already exists for this Applicability.

Connector: Microsoft Dataverse → List rows
Table name: Evidences (or whatever the plural is — confirm with what the connector offers)
Filter rows: click fx → paste this expression:

concat('_pei_applicability_value eq ', items('Loop_Active_Applicability')?['pei_applicabilityid'])

Select columns: pei_evidenceid (minimum — we just need to know if any row exists)
Row count: 1 (we only need to know if ≥1 exists; no point fetching more)
Rename the action to: Find Existing Evidence

Action 3 — Condition: No Evidence Exists

Connector: Control → Condition
Condition: click fx → paste:

length(outputs('Find_Existing_Evidence')?['body/value'])

Middle dropdown: is equal to
Right value: 0
Rename the condition to: No Evidence Exists

Action 4 — Add a new row: Create Evidence Gap
This goes INSIDE the True branch of No Evidence Exists.

Connector: Microsoft Dataverse → Add a new row
Table name: Evidences

Field values to set:

Name (primary column for Evidence) — click fx, paste:

concat('Evidence - ', items('Loop_Active_Applicability')?['_pei_controlprocedure_value@OData.Community.Display.V1.FormattedValue'], ' - ', items('Loop_Active_Applicability')?['_pei_application_value@OData.Community.Display.V1.FormattedValue'])
This builds a friendly name like Evidence - CPROC-TEST-APPLEVEL-01 - APP_0005.

Applicability (lookup) — click fx, paste:

concat('pei_applicabilities(', items('Loop_Active_Applicability')?['pei_applicabilityid'], ')')

Control Procedure (lookup) — click fx, paste:

concat('pei_controlprocedures(', items('Loop_Active_Applicability')?['_pei_controlprocedure_value'], ')')

Application (lookup) — click fx, paste:

concat('pei_applications(', items('Loop_Active_Applicability')?['_pei_application_value'], ')')

Import Cycle (lookup) — click fx, paste:

concat('pei_importcycles(', variables('varImportCycleID'), ')')

Evidence Status — select from dropdown: Gap (value 890920003)

Rename the action to: Create Evidence Gap
Action 5 (optional but recommended) — Compose: Skipped Existing Evidence
This goes INSIDE the False branch of No Evidence Exists.
Purpose: mark that we skipped a row for audit trace (useful during regression testing).

Connector: Data Operation → Compose
Inputs: click fx, paste:

concat('Skipped - Evidence already exists for applicability ', items('Loop_Active_Applicability')?['pei_applicabilityid'])

Rename the action to: Skipped Existing Evidence

You can remove this Compose action after you've validated idempotency works. It's purely for visibility during testing.

What this builds
For every eligible Applicability in the cycle:

If no Evidence exists → create one with status Gap
If Evidence already exists → skip it, log a trace

On first Stage 3 gate tick: creates N Evidence records.
On re-tick: zero new Evidence records (all already exist).
On a cycle where some Applicabilities were added after first tick: only new ones get Evidence.
